description.narrative: UNICEF in collaboration with UNDP supported the Government of Nepal to develop disaster risk reduction and management policy and action plan in four of the seven Provinces and roll out Disaster Management Information System in two Provinces. 19 municipalities prepared risk profiles and five of them developed risk informed annual plans; 14 municipalities drafted DRM law and DRM fund mobilization guidelines and allocated and utilized resources on disaster risk mitigation action. A total of 65,557 people (F: 31,649) benefited from lifesaving humanitarian response while 200,000 people received hygiene promotion following small scale disasters across various parts of the country. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/12/2019
